s. How do games accomplish this and to what end? The contributors explore the video game as an atmospheric medium of hitherto unimagined potential. Is the medium too powerful, too influential? A danger to our mental health or an ally through even the darkest of times? This volume compiles papers from the Young Academics Workshop at the Clash of Realities conferences of 2019 and 2020 to provide answers to these questions.  afunded by BMBF Fördervorhaben 16TOA002  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSocial sciences. 4aAmbience. 4aAtmosphere. 4aComputer Games. 4aMedia Aesthetics. 4aMedia Studies. 4aMedia. 4aMedicine. 4aMental Health. 4aPlay. 4aPopular Culture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aAmbience.  aAtmosphere.  aComputer Games.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia.  aMedicine.  aMental Health.  aPlay.  aPopular Culture.1 aAguilar Rodríguez, Jimena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAguilar Rodríguez, Jimena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAller, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlvarez Igarzábal, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlvarez Igarzábal, Federico, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAugusto Bordini, Rogério, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBühler, Nils, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDebus, Michael S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDebus, Michael S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/voca